        "supplementing",
        "commenting"
      ],
      "body": [
        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "value": " Grettir hates his father very much, and he has good reason to. His father won't give him a sword, and he resents that very bitterly. And his mother provides him-- secretly provides him with the sword. INAUDIBLE makes up the poem. And, after all, the mother is a friend of the man. And this uses an entirely Freudian symbol in an entirely conscious way. It seems to me to show how old that consciousness is of the personality which we treat with such great novelty.",
          "format": "text/plain",
          "purpose": "commenting"
        },
        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "value": "Anthony West",
          "format": "text/plain",
          "purpose": "tagging"
        },
        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "value": "August 5 Session Discussion",
