        "supplementing",
        "commenting"
      ],
      "body": [
        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "value": " Then he is taken up by the community, which is outraged. And the people who condemn him, they say quite simply-- they think they're being very humane and very liberal. We only ask one price for a man's life, and that is a man's life. The INAUDIBLE, who has avenged his brother, is then taken to-- put in a prison and put in a prison cell. And the penalty is not exactly-- it's very violent form. All he has to do is wait till the time he dies. And there is a man there who is in the same position, who is waiting for death too.",
          "format": "text/plain",
          "purpose": "commenting"
        },
        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "value": "Anthony West",
          "format": "text/plain",
          "purpose": "tagging"
        },
